{"lemma":"أَزِقَّة","slug":"أَزِقَّة","root":"ز.ق.ق","root_slug":"ز-ق-ق","root_link":"/words/roots/ز-ق-ق","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n17897","n17898","n17899"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D8%B2%D9%90%D9%82%D9%8E%D9%91%D8%A9"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"alley, lane, corridor"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"With progressive dissimilation in voicedness (compare for this phenomenon in a like measure رُزْدَاق (ruzdāq) and قَتَاد (qatād)) from Aramaic 𐡔𐡒𐡒𐡀 / 𐡵𐡳𐡳𐡠 / שְׁקָקָא / ܫܩܳܩܳܐ (šəqāqā), from Akkadian 𒋢𒋡𒄣𒌑 (su-qa-qu-u₂ /⁠suqāqu⁠/), which is the diminutive of the same word as present in سُوق (sūq)."},"ipa":["/zu.qaːq/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n17897","headword_ar":"زَقَاقٌ","root":"zq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zaq~aAqN","text_ar":"زَقَّاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n17898","headword_ar":"زُقَاقٌ","root":"zq","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sik~ap","text_ar":"سِكَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"street"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, K:) or [rather"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a by-street,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lane;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a narrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tariyq","text_ar":"طَرِيق"},{"kind":"text","text":"[here meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"street"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"less than a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sik~ap","text_ar":"سِكَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, Mgh, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whether a thoroughfare or not:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb:) masc. (S, Msb) and fem.: (S, Msb, K:) Akh says that the people of El-Hijáz make"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlT~ariyqu","text_ar":"الطَّرِيقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~iraATu","text_ar":"الصِّرَاطُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~abiylu","text_ar":"السَّبِيلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~uwqu","text_ar":"السُّوقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alz~uqaAqu","text_ar":"الزُّقَاقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alkal~aA='u","text_ar":"الكَلَّا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is the market of El-Basrah, (S,) fem.; and Temeem make them masc., (S, Msb,) i. e. all of these: (S:) pl. [of pauc., but also used as a pl. of mult.,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aziq~apN","text_ar":"اَزِقَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Mgh, Msb, K) and [of mult.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zuq~aAnN","text_ar":"زُقَّانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Sb, S, M, K.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mano hadaYzuqaAqFA","text_ar":"مَنْ هَدَىزُقَاقًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", occurring in a trad., means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He who has guided the erring and the blind to his way."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alz~uqaAqu","text_ar":"الزُّقَاقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The strait of Gibraltar;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the passage of the sea between Tanjeh and El-Jezeereh el-Khad- rà, in the west,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by El-Andalus; called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zuqaAqu sabotapa","text_ar":"زُقَاقُ سَبْتَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","M","Mgh","Msb","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n17899","headword_ar":"زَقَّاقٌ","root":"zq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"maker of the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"kind of skin called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ziq~","text_ar":"زِقّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)       -A2-  Also, as in the copies of the Moheet and the A [and in the JK], or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zaqaAqN","text_ar":"زَقَاقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saHaAbN","text_ar":"سَحَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", accord. to the K, but the former is probably the right, (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"One who drinks water"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Moheet,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A,"},{"kind":"text","text":"K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"at the table,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Moheet, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"while having food in his mouth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Moheet, A, K.) [As shown in the A, it is an epithet applied to a greedy man.]"}],"source_refs":["TA","Moheet","K"]}]}}